<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-501-893  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 501 893.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Oct 15 1990 v7 n42 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Firm swaps out IBM host for distributed AS/400 net. (Fluor Daniel)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smith, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fluor Daniel Inc is changing its centralized mainframe network toa distributed network by installing IBM Corp's AS/400minicomputers in its headquarters.andP;  Eventually the company plansto link as many as 50 AS/400's using IBM's Advanced Peer-to-PeerNetworking (APPN) throughout its international network.andP;  Therestructuring of Fluor Daniel's network goes along with thecompany's distributed organizational structure and will moveprocessing power closer to end users.andP;  The shift to a distributednetwork will also improve communications among the company's manyunits and will pave the way for cooperative applicationprocessing.andP;  The distributed architecture will let users handlelocal processing and upload summary information to Fluor Daniel'sheadquarters.andP;  The network will also offer support of electronicmail and communications among computer-aided design systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Fluor Daniel Inc. (communication systems)International Business Machines Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Network ManagementReorganizationDistributed Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartphotograph.andO;Caption:   Fluor Daniel goes distributed. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>